[22:27] <pmichaud> bsdz: PCT isn't intended to directly support every operation one might imagine.
[22:27] <pmichaud> instead, it provides common primitives to make whatever operation might be wanted
[22:28] <pmichaud> so, in the case of attempting to convert a scalar to an aggregate, either the PMC itself should do it, or the thing generating the PAST should do the checks for an aggregate prior to attempting the assignment
[22:28] <pmichaud> It's also possible to create custom PAST node behaviors (derive from PAST::*  and override the behavior)
[22:29] <pmichaud> one could also set an exception handler that traps the "get_pmc_keyed in class Integer" and decides how to handle it.
